{"id":23274,"title":"Exact vs. approximate computation: reconciling different estimates of Mycobacterium tuberculosis epidemiological parameters.","abstract":"Exact computational methods for inference in population genetics are intuitively preferable to approximate analyses. We reconcile two starkly different estimates of the reproductive number of tuberculosis from previous studies that used the same genotyping data and underlying model. This demonstrates the value of approximate analyses in validating exact methods. ","date":"2014-04-11","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24496011","annotations":[{"name":"Numerical analysis","weight":0.802814,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numerical_analysis"},{"name":"Data","weight":0.703484,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data"},{"name":"Population genetics","weight":0.696901,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population_genetics"},{"name":"Computation","weight":0.542155,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computation"},{"name":"Inference","weight":0.487222,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inference"},{"name":"Population","weight":0.424859,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population"},{"name":"Conceptual model","weight":0.41588,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conceptual_model"},{"name":"Epidemiology","weight":0.370553,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemiology"},{"name":"Genetics","weight":0.270553,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetics"},{"name":"Intuition (knowledge)","weight":0.190671,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intuition_(knowledge)"},{"name":"Reproduction","weight":0.153647,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reproduction"},{"name":"Computational chemistry","weight":0.0886352,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_chemistry"},{"name":"Geno